    "faq_8XYCd7": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "question_kkQ9cg": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What does this bundle include?",
            "text": "<p>This bundle includes the Arccos Air wearable with a charging case, the Arccos Smart Laser rangefinder with a carry case, and the first year's Game Tracking and Smart Laser subscription.</p><p>Together, Air automatically tracks your shots to provide a detailed breakdown of your game, while Smart Laser provides precise “Plays Like” yardages adjusting for slope and weather conditions — helping you play your smartest golf.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_Xzd3JJ": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Do I need an Arccos membership to use the bundle?",
            "text": "<p>The bundle includes your first year's Game Tracking and Smart Laser subscription, so you can start using all features right away. <br/><br/>Your membership unlocks the full Arccos experience, including:<br/></p><ul><li>Automatic shot tracking</li><li>Strokes Gained performance analytics</li><li>AI-powered strategy insights</li><li>Smart Club Distances</li><li>Green Maps (where available)</li><li>Weather-adjusted “Plays Like” distances</li></ul>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_mBKjNB": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How accurate is the Smart Laser rangefinder?",
            "text": "<p>The Arccos Smart Laser is accurate to within ±1 yard.</p><p>It measures precise line-of-sight distance, then adjusts for slope, wind speed, wind gusts, wind direction, temperature, and humidity to calculate a true “Plays Like” yardage. This means you’re not just getting distance — you’re getting the correct number for the conditions you’re playing in.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_rXdYVi": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How does Arccos track my shots without sensors?",
            "text": "<p>Arccos Air is an AI wearable golf tracker that automatically detects your shots during the round.<br/>You still get full access to Arccos insights like Strokes Gained analytics, scoring breakdowns, and performance trends without attaching sensors to your clubs. If you want deeper club-level tracking, you can optionally add AI-assisted club tagging, manual tagging, or Arccos Smart Sensors — but none are required to use the system.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_73aEUt": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How many rounds do I need before Arccos provides useful insights?",
            "text": "<p>Just one round.</p><p>After your first round you’ll receive:<br/></p><ul><li>A full Strokes Gained breakdown</li><li>Scoring insights</li><li>Smart Club Distances</li><li>and more</li></ul><p>As you play more rounds, Arccos continues to refine your performance trends and recommendations.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_zjbNjq": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How is the Smart Laser different from a standard rangefinder with slope?",
            "text": "<p>Most golf rangefinders stop at slope-adjusted distance.</p><p>The Arccos Smart Laser goes further by factoring in wind speed, wind gusts, wind direction, temperature, and humidity in addition to slope. This produces a true “Plays Like” distance that reflects real playing conditions.</p><p>Combined with Arccos game tracking, it helps you choose the right club with greater confidence.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_micPEW": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Is the Smart Laser & Air legal for tournament play?",
            "text": "<p>Yes — when Tournament Mode is enabled.</p><p>Smart Laser conforming mode disables slope and environmental adjustments so the rangefinder complies with the Rules of Golf for tournament play.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_TAHjK6": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Do professional golfers use Arccos?",
            "text": "<p>Yes. Major Champion Matt Fitzpatrick uses Arccos performance data and Smart Laser distance insights to help refine strategy and dial in yardages.</p><p>Arccos is designed to bring that same data-driven approach to improvement to golfers of every level.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_yVM9Gw": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What happens if I lose or damage my Smart Laser or Air?",
            "text": "<p>If your Smart Laser rangefinder, or Air, is lost or damaged, you can purchase a replacement device for a one-time fee. Your Arccos membership remains active and stays connected to your account.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_4RQzVE": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Are Green Maps available worldwide?",
            "text": "<p>Currently, Arccos Green Maps are available for courses within the United States.</p><p>Our team is actively working to expand Green Maps internationally. Updates will be shared in the Arccos app and on our support site as new countries and regions become available.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_UNEbmP": {
          "type": "question",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "title": "Does Arccos Air work on Android?",
            "text": "<p>At launch, sensorless tracking with Arccos Air requires an iPhone.</p><p>Android support is coming soon. In the meantime, Android users can pair Arccos Air with Smart Sensors to enable full shot tracking and performance insights.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        }
      },
